      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Certainly! An escrow account is a neutral third-party account that holds funds during the property buying and selling process. In a real estate transaction, it ensures that money, such as the down payment or other agreed-upon expenses, is securely held until all parts of the deal meet agreed-upon terms, including inspections and loan processing. It provides peace of mind to both buyers and sellers by safeguarding the transaction and ensuring funds are only exchanged when the terms are fulfilled.",
